oop_type {:?}\",\n   466→                    loop_state.loop_number, loop_state.loop_type\n   467→                ));\n   468→            }\n   469→\n   470→            if !seen.insert(loop_state.loop_number) {\n   471→                return Err(format!(\n   472→                    \"duplicate loop_number {} found across state arrays\",\n   473→                    loop_state.loop_number\n   474→                ));\n   475→            }\n   476→        }\n   477→\n   478→        for attempt in &self.completion_attempts {\n   479→            if attempt.loop_type != LoopType::Completion {\n   480→                return Err(format!(\n   481→                    \"completion loop {} has invalid loop_type {:?}\",\n   482→                    attempt.loop_number, attempt.loop_type\n   483→                ));\n   484→            }\n   485→\n   486→            if attempt.slug != \"completion\" {\n   487→                return Err(format!(\n   488→                    \"completion loop {} must use slug 'completion', got '{}'\",\n   489→                    attempt.loop_number, attempt.slug\n   490→                ));\n   491→            }\n   492→\n   493→            if !seen.insert(attempt.loop_number) {\n   494→                return Err(format!(\n   495→                    \"duplicate loop_number {} found across state arrays\",\n   496→                    attempt.loop_number\n   497→                ));\n   498→            }\n   499→        }\n   500→\n   501→        if self.current_loop == 0 {\n   502→            if !seen.is_empty() {\n   503→                return Err(\"current_loop is 0 but loop entries exist\".to_owned());\n   504→            }\n   505→        } else if !seen.contains(&self.current_loop) {\n   506→            return Err(format!(\n   507→                \"current_loop {} does not refer to any loop entry\",\n   508→                self.current_loop\n   509→            ));\n   510→        }\n   511→\n   512→        Ok(())\n   513→    }\n   514→}\n   515→\n   516→impl QuickDevPhase {\n   517→    /// Map a quick-dev phase to the corresponding compatibility `Phase` used\n   518→    /// for git checkpoint messaging and state persistence.\n   519→    pub fn to_current_phase(&self) -> Phase {\n   520→        match self {\n   521→            QuickDevPhase::PlanAndImplement => Phase::Implementing,\n   522→            QuickDevPhase::CodexReview => Phase::Reviewing,\n   523→            QuickDevPhase::ApplyFixes => Phase::Implementing,\n   524→            QuickDevPhase::FinalReview => Phase::FinalReview,\n   525→        }\n   526→    }\n   527→}\n   528→\n   529→impl std::fmt::Display for QuickDevPhase {\n   530→    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {\n   531→        match self {\n   532→            QuickDevPhase::PlanAndImplement => write!(f, \"plan_and_implement\"),\n   533→            QuickDevPhase::CodexReview => write!(f, \"codex_review\"),\n   534→            QuickDevPhase::ApplyFixes => write!(f, \"apply_fixes\"),\n   535→            QuickDevPhase::FinalReview => write!(f, \"final_review\"),\n   536→        }\n   537→    }\n   538→}\n   539→\n   540→impl CompletionLoopArtifacts {\n   541→    pub fn has_acceptance_result_for(&self, backend: &str) -> bool {\n   542→        self.acceptance_results\n   543→            .iter()\n   544→            .any(|result| result.backend == backend)\n   545→    }\n   546→\n   547→    pub fn upsert_acceptance_result(&mut self, result: AcceptanceQaResult) {\n   548→        if let Some(existing) = self\n   549→            .acceptance_results\n   550→            .iter_mut()\n   551→            .find(|existing| existing.backend == result.backend)\n   552→        {\n   553→            *existing = result;\n   554→            return;\n   555→        }\n   556→\n   557→        self.acceptance_results.push(result);\n   558→    }\n   559→\n   560→    pub fn acceptance_all_required_passed(&self, required: &[&str]) -> bool {\n   561→        required.iter().all(|backend| {\n   562→            self.acceptance_results\n   563→                .iter()\n   564→                .any(|result| result.backend == *backend && result.passed)\n   565→        })\n   566→    }\n   567→\n   568→    pub fn acceptance_any_required_failed(&self, required: &[&str]) -> bool {\n   569→        required.iter().any(|backend| {\n   570→            self.acceptance_results\n   571→                .iter()\n   572→                .any(|result| result.backend == *backend && !result.passed)\n   573→        })\n   574→    }\n   575→}\n   576→\n   577→#[cfg(test)]\n   578→mod tests {\n   579→    use super::{default_created_at, ProjectState, QuickDevPhase};\n   580→    use chrono::{DateTime, Utc};\n   581→\n   582→    #[test]\n   583→    fn new_state_defaults_prompt_review_completed_to_false() {\n   584→        let state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   585→        assert!(!state.prompt_review_completed);\n   586→    }\n   587→\n   588→    #[test]\n   589→    fn new_state_defaults_quick_dev_phase_to_none() {\n   590→        let state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   591→        assert!(state.quick_dev_phase.is_none());\n   592→    }\n   593→\n   594→    #[test]\n   595→    fn legacy_state_without_prompt_review_field_deserializes_to_false() {\n   596→        let state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   597→        let mut value = serde_json::to_value(&state).expect(\"serialize state\");\n   598→        value\n   599→            .as_object_mut()\n   600→            .expect(\"state should serialize as object\")\n   601→            .remove(\"prompt_review_completed\");\n   602→\n   603→        let parsed: ProjectState = serde_json::from_value(value).expect(\"deserialize legacy state\");\n   604→        assert!(!parsed.prompt_review_completed);\n   605→    }\n   606→\n   607→    #[test]\n   608→    fn legacy_state_without_quick_dev_phase_deserializes_to_none() {\n   609→        let state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   610→        let mut value = serde_json::to_value(&state).expect(\"serialize state\");\n   611→        value\n   612→            .as_object_mut()\n   613→            .expect(\"state should serialize as object\")\n   614→            .remove(\"quick_dev_phase\");\n   615→\n   616→        let parsed: ProjectState = serde_json::from_value(value).expect(\"deserialize legacy state\");\n   617→        assert!(parsed.quick_dev_phase.is_none());\n   618→    }\n   619→\n   620→    #[test]\n   621→    fn state_roundtrip_preserves_quick_dev_phase() {\n   622→        let mut state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   623→        state.quick_dev_phase = Some(QuickDevPhase::ApplyFixes);\n   624→\n   625→        let serialized = serde_json::to_string(&state).expect(\"serialize state\");\n   626→        let parsed: ProjectState = serde_json::from_str(&serialized).expect(\"deserialize state\");\n   627→        assert_eq!(parsed.quick_dev_phase, Some(QuickDevPhase::ApplyFixes));\n   628→    }\n   629→\n   630→    #[test]\n   631→    fn new_state_sets_created_at() {\n   632→        let before = Utc::now();\n   633→        let state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   634→        let after = Utc::now();\n   635→        assert!(state.created_at >= before);\n   636→        assert!(state.created_at <= after);\n   637→    }\n   638→\n   639→    #[test]\n   640→    fn legacy_state_without_created_at_deserializes_to_sentinel() {\n   641→        let state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   642→        let mut value = serde_json::to_value(&state).expect(\"serialize state\");\n   643→        value\n   644→            .as_object_mut()\n   645→            .expect(\"state should serialize as object\")\n   646→            .remove(\"created_at\");\n   647→\n   648→        let parsed: ProjectState = serde_json::from_value(value).expect(\"deserialize legacy state\");\n   649→        assert_eq!(parsed.created_at, DateTime::<Utc>::MIN_UTC);\n   650→        assert_eq!(parsed.created_at, default_created_at());\n   651→    }\n   652→\n   653→    #[test]\n   654→    fn legacy_state_without_session_store_deserializes_to_empty() {\n   655→        let state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   656→        let mut value = serde_json::to_value(&state).expect(\"serialize state\");\n   657→        value\n   658→            .as_object_mut()\n   659→            .expect(\"state should serialize as object\")\n   660→            .remove(\"session_store\");\n   661→\n   662→        let parsed: ProjectState = serde_json::from_value(value).expect(\"deserialize legacy state\");\n   663→        assert!(parsed.session_store.records.is_empty());\n   664→    }\n   665→\n   666→    #[test]\n   667→    fn session_store_lookup_finds_matching_record() {\n   668→        use super::SessionStore;\n   669→        let mut store = SessionStore::default();\n   670→        store.upsert(super::SessionRecord {\n   671→            session_id: \"sid-1\".to_owned(),\n   672→            backend_spec: \"claude(opus)\".to_owned(),\n   673→            role: \"implementer\".to_owned(),\n   674→            loop_number: 1,\n   675→            bootstrap_hash: \"hash1\".to_owned(),\n   676→            call_count: 1,\n   677→            created_at: Utc::now(),\n   678→            last_used_at: Utc::now(),\n   679→        });\n   680→\n   681→        assert!(store.lookup(1, \"implementer\", \"claude(opus)\").is_some());\n   682→        assert!(store.lookup(1, \"reviewer\", \"claude(opus)\").is_none());\n   683→        assert!(store.lookup(2, \"implementer\", \"claude(opus)\").is_none());\n   684→        assert!(store.lookup(1, \"implementer\", \"codex\").is_none());\n   685→    }\n   686→\n   687→    #[test]\n   688→    fn session_store_upsert_replaces_existing_record() {\n   689→        use super::{SessionRecord, SessionStore};\n   690→        let mut store = SessionStore::default();\n   691→        let now = Utc::now();\n   692→        store.upsert(SessionRecord {\n   693→            session_id: \"sid-old\".to_owned(),\n   694→            backend_spec: \"claude\".to_owned(),\n   695→            role: \"qa\".to_owned(),\n   696→            loop_number: 2,\n   697→            bootstrap_hash: \"hash\".to_owned(),\n   698→            call_count: 1,\n   699→            created_at: now,\n   700→            last_used_at: now,\n   701→        });\n   702→        store.upsert(SessionRecord {\n   703→            session_id: \"sid-new\".to_owned(),\n   704→            backend_spec: \"claude\".to_owned(),\n   705→            role: \"qa\".to_owned(),\n   706→            loop_number: 2,\n   707→            bootstrap_hash: \"hash\".to_owned(),\n   708→            call_count: 2,\n   709→            created_at: now,\n   710→            last_used_at: now,\n   711→        });\n   712→        assert_eq!(store.records.len(), 1);\n   713→        assert_eq!(store.records[0].session_id, \"sid-new\");\n   714→        assert_eq!(store.records[0].call_count, 2);\n   715→    }\n   716→\n   717→    #[test]\n   718→    fn session_store_remove_for_loop_clears_matching_records() {\n   719→        use super::{SessionRecord, SessionStore};\n   720→        let mut store = SessionStore::default();\n   721→        let now = Utc::now();\n   722→        for (loop_number, role) in [(1, \"implementer\"), (1, \"reviewer\"), (2, \"implementer\")] {\n   723→            store.upsert(SessionRecord {\n   724→                session_id: format!(\"sid-{loop_number}-{role}\"),\n   725→                backend_spec: \"claude\".to_owned(),\n   726→                role: role.to_owned(),\n   727→                loop_number,\n   728→                bootstrap_hash: \"h\".to_owned(),\n   729→                call_count: 1,\n   730→                created_at: now,\n   731→                last_used_at: now,\n   732→            });\n   733→        }\n   734→        assert_eq!(store.records.len(), 3);\n   735→        store.remove_for_loop(1);\n   736→        assert_eq!(store.records.len(), 1);\n   737→        assert_eq!(store.records[0].loop_number, 2);\n   738→    }\n   739→\n   740→    #[test]\n   741→    fn session_store_serde_roundtrip() {\n   742→        use super::{SessionRecord, SessionStore};\n   743→        let now = Utc::now();\n   744→        let mut store = SessionStore::default();\n   745→        store.upsert(SessionRecord {\n   746→            session_id: \"sid-rt\".to_owned(),\n   747→            backend_spec: \"codex(gpt-5.3-codex-high)\".to_owned(),\n   748→            role: \"reviewer\".to_owned(),\n   749→            loop_number: 3,\n   750→            bootstrap_hash: \"abcd1234\".to_owned(),\n   751→            call_count: 5,\n   752→            created_at: now,\n   753→            last_used_at: now,\n   754→        });\n   755→        let json = serde_json::to_string(&store).expect(\"serialize session store\");\n   756→        let parsed: SessionStore = serde_json::from_str(&json).expect(\"deserialize session store\");\n   757→        assert_eq!(parsed.records.len(), 1);\n   758→        assert_eq!(parsed.records[0].session_id, \"sid-rt\");\n   759→        assert_eq!(parsed.records[0].call_count, 5);\n   760→    }\n   761→\n   762→    #[test]\n   763→    fn new_state_initializes_empty_session_store() {\n   764→        let state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   765→        assert!(state.session_store.records.is_empty());\n   766→    }\n   767→\n   768→    #[test]\n   769→    fn remove_loop_clears_session_records() {\n   770→        use super::SessionRecord;\n   771→        let mut state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   772→        let now = Utc::now();\n   773→        state.session_store.upsert(SessionRecord {\n   774→            session_id: \"sid-1\".to_owned(),\n   775→            backend_spec: \"claude\".to_owned(),\n   776→            role: \"implementer\".to_owned(),\n   777→            loop_number: 1,\n   778→            bootstrap_hash: \"h\".to_owned(),\n   779→            call_count: 1,\n   780→            created_at: now,\n   781→            last_used_at: now,\n   782→        });\n   783→        state.session_store.upsert(SessionRecord {\n   784→            session_id: \"sid-2\".to_owned(),\n   785→            backend_spec: \"claude\".to_owned(),\n   786→            role: \"reviewer\".to_owned(),\n   787→            loop_number: 2,\n   788→            bootstrap_hash: \"h\".to_owned(),\n   789→            call_count: 1,\n   790→            created_at: now,\n   791→            last_used_at: now,\n   792→        });\n   793→        // remove_loop must clear session records for that loop (spec D1)\n   794→        state.remove_loop(1);\n   795→        assert_eq!(\n   796→            state.session_store.records.len(),\n   797→            1,\n   798→            \"only loop 2 session should remain\"\n   799→        );\n   800→        assert_eq!(state.session_store.records[0].loop_number, 2);\n   801→    }\n   802→\n   803→    #[test]\n   804→    fn final_review_requires_iteration_one() {\n   805→        let mut state = ProjectState::new(\"demo\", \"Demo\", \"abc123\", None);\n   806→        state.current_phase = super::Phase::FinalReview;\n   807→        state.phase_iteration = 2;\n   808→        let err = state\n   809→            .validate_invariants()\n   810→            .expect_err(\"final_review iteration > 1 should fail\");\n   811→        assert!(err.contains(\"final_review\"));\n   812→    }\n   813→}\n   814→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01D1YGYYF5pXopdBJ1HtvaN6","session_id":"3d9a0615-7442-4a66-ab27-f8160d110223","uuid":"8b0bebc1-18f2-4601-8699-9d96fba9c39e"}
