{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015UBZ4JVrmK3iBgEnHWXFGU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my findings into a comprehensive report.\n\n## CLI Command Implementation Verification Report\n\nBased on my comprehensive search of the ralph-burning-rewrite Rust project, I have verified all 28 required CLI subcommands against the actual implementation. Here are my findings:\n\n### Summary\n**Result: 16 out of 28 commands are MISSING from the implementation**\n\n### Detailed Analysis\n\n#### Workspace/Config - 5/5 ✓ IMPLEMENTED\n- `ralph init` ✓ (InitArgs in Commands enum)\n- `ralph config show` ✓ (ConfigCommand::Show)\n- `ralph config get <key>` ✓ (ConfigCommand::Get)\n- `ralph config set <key> <value>` ✓ (ConfigCommand::Set)\n- `ralph config edit` ✓ (ConfigCommand::Edit)\n\n#### Flow Discovery - 0/2 ✗ MISSING\n- `ralph flow list` ✗ NOT FOUND\n- `ralph flow show <flow-id>` ✗ NOT FOUND\n\n#### Projects - 5/5 ✓ IMPLEMENTED\n- `ralph project create --id <id> --name <name> --prompt <file> --flow <flow-id>` ✓ (ProjectCommand::New)\n  - Note: Uses `--from` instead of `--flow` but serves same purpose\n- `ralph project select <id>` ✓ (ProjectCommand::Use)\n- `ralph project list` ✓ (ProjectCommand::List)\n- `ralph project show [<id>]` ✓ (ProjectCommand::Show)\n- `ralph project delete <id>` ✓ (ProjectCommand::Delete)\n\n#### Run Lifecycle - 2/6 ✗ PARTIALLY IMPLEMENTED (2 missing)\n- `ralph run start` ✓ (Run command exists - treated as default/main run behavior)\n- `ralph run resume` ✗ NOT FOUND (no subcommand; would need separate Resume command)\n- `ralph run status` ✗ NOT FOUND (exists as separate `ralph status` command instead)\n- `ralph run history` ✗ NOT FOUND (exists as separate `ralph history` command instead)\n- `ralph run tail [--logs]` ✗ NOT FOUND (exists as separate `ralph tail` command instead)\n- `ralph run rollback --to <target> [--hard]` ✗ NOT FOUND (exists as separate `ralph rollback` command instead)\n\n#### Requirements - 0/4 ✗ MISSING\n- `ralph requirements draft --idea \"<text>\"` ✗ NOT FOUND\n- `ralph requirements quick --idea \"<text>\"` ✗ NOT FOUND\n- `ralph requirements show <run-id>` ✗ NOT FOUND\n- `ralph requirements answer <run-id>` ✗ NOT FOUND\n\n#### Daemon - 4/5 ✗ PARTIALLY IMPLEMENTED (1 name mismatch)\n- `ralph daemon start` ✓ (DaemonCommand::Start)\n- `ralph daemon status` ✓ (DaemonCommand::Status)\n- `ralph daemon abort <task-id>` ✓ (DaemonCommand::Abort)\n- `ralph daemon retry <task-id>` ✗ NAMED DIFFERENTLY (called `Retrigger` instead of `Retry`)\n- `ralph daemon reconcile` ✗ NOT FOUND\n\n#### Conformance - 0/2 ✗ MISSING\n- `ralph conformance list` ✗ NOT FOUND\n- `ralph conformance run [--filter <scenario-id>]` ✗ NOT FOUND (Note: there's a `validate` command but not `conformance`)\n\n### Existing Commands Not in Requirements\nThe implementation includes these additional commands not in the specification:\n- `ralph prd` (PRD generator)\n- `ralph quick-prd` (Quick PRD variant)\n- `ralph auto` (Automatic mode)\n- `ralph quick-dev-run` (Quick dev run variant)\n- `ralph quick-dev-auto` (Quick dev auto variant)\n- `ralph backend` (Backend management)\n- `ralph validate` (Validation/conformance testing)\n- `ralph amend` (Amendment functionality)\n\n### Key Structural Differences\n1. **Subcommand Organization**: Many commands that should be subcommands of `run` (resume, status, history, tail, rollback) are implemented as top-level commands instead\n2. **Requirements Module**: Completely missing - no `requirements` command family\n3. **Flow Discovery**: Completely missing - no `flow` command family  \n4. **Conformance Commands**: Missing dedicated `conformance` command (validation tests exist separately)\n5. **Daemon Reconcile**: Missing reconciliation command\n\n### File Locations for Implementation\n- Main CLI definitions: `/root/new-ralph-burning/multibackend-orchestration/src/cli/mod.rs`\n- Daemon subcommands: `/root/new-ralph