{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012WdzA69zjKMBsJZJXJLEj3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→//! PRD stage prompt builders and deterministic output parsers.\n     2→\n     3→use std::collections::BTreeMap;\n     4→\n     5→use crate::workflow::parser::strip_frontmatter;\n     6→\n     7→use super::state::Stage;\n     8→\n     9→// ============================================================================\n    10→// Embedded Stage Prompt Templates\n    11→// ============================================================================\n    12→\n    13→const IDEATION_PROMPT: &str = r#\"You are a product ideation specialist. Generate comprehensive ideation content for the following product idea.\n    14→\n    15→**Product Idea:**\n    16→{{idea}}\n    17→\n    18→**User-Provided Context:**\n    19→{{answers}}\n    20→\n    21→**Required Output Format:**\n    22→Your response must be a markdown document with the following exact section headings:\n    23→\n    24→## Core Concept\n    25→## Target Users\n    26→## Key Problems Solved\n    27→## Proposed Features\n    28→## Success Metrics\n    29→## Constraints & Assumptions\n    30→\n    31→Each section should be substantive and specific to the product idea.\n    32→\"#;\n    33→\n    34→const RESEARCH_PROMPT: &str = r#\"You are a technical research analyst. Conduct research for the following product idea.\n    35→\n    36→**Product Idea:**\n    37→{{idea}}\n    38→\n    39→**User-Provided Context:**\n    40→{{answers}}\n    41→\n    42→**Ideation Output:**\n    43→{{ideation}}\n    44→\n    45→**Required Output Format:**\n    46→Your response must be a markdown document with the following exact section headings:\n    47→\n    48→## Market Context\n    49→## Technical Landscape\n    50→## Comparable Solutions\n    51→## Technical Feasibility\n    52→## Risk Assessment\n    53→\n    54→Each section should be substantive and specific to the product idea.\n    55→\"#;\n    56→\n    57→const SYNTHESIS_PROMPT: &str = r#\"You are a product strategist. Synthesize ideation and research into a coherent product strategy.\n    58→\n    59→**Product Idea:**\n    60→{{idea}}\n    61→\n    62→**User-Provided Context:**\n    63→{{answers}}\n    64→\n    65→**Ideation Output:**\n    66→{{ideation}}\n    67→\n    68→**Research Output:**\n    69→{{research}}\n    70→\n    71→**Required Output Format:**\n    72→Your response must be a markdown document with the following exact section headings:\n    73→\n    74→## Product Vision\n    75→## User Stories\n    76→## Feature Prioritization\n    77→## Architecture Overview\n    78→## MVP Scope\n    79→## Open Questions\n    80→\n    81→Each section should be substantive and specific to the product idea.\n    82→\"#;\n    83→\n    84→const PRD_PROMPT: &str = r#\"You are a technical product manager. Generate a comprehensive Product Requirements Document (PRD) for the following product idea.\n    85→\n    86→**Product Idea:**\n    87→{{idea}}\n    88→\n    89→**User-Provided Context:**\n    90→{{answers}}\n    91→\n    92→**Ideation Output:**\n    93→{{ideation}}\n    94→\n    95→**Research Output:**\n    96→{{research}}\n    97→\n    98→**Synthesis Output:**\n    99→{{synthesis}}\n   100→\n   101→**Required Output Format:**\n   102→Your response must be a markdown document with the following exact section headings:\n   103→\n   104→## Executive Summary\n   105→## Goals & Non-Goals\n   106→## User Stories\n   107→## Functional Requirements\n   108→## Non-Functional Requirements\n   109→## Technical Architecture\n   110→## Data Model\n   111→## API Design\n   112→## Security Considerations\n   113→## Testing Strategy\n   114→## Rollout Plan\n   115→## Success Metrics\n   116→## Open Questions\n   117→\n   118→Each section should be substantive and specific to the product idea.\n   119→\"#;\n   120→\n   121→const GAP_ANALYSIS_PROMPT: &str = r#\"You are a requirements analyst. Analyze the following {{stage_name}} output for information gaps, missing fields, ambiguities, and questions that need clarification.\n   122→\n   123→**Product Idea:**\n   124→{{idea}}\n   125→\n   126→**User-Provided Context:**\n   127→{{answers}}\n   128→\n   129→**{{stage_name}} Output:**\n   130→{{stage_output}}\n   131→\n   132→**Task:**\n   133→Identify any missing information, ambiguities, or questions that should be asked to the user to improve the {{stage_name}} output.\n   134→\n   135→**Required Output Format:**\n   136→Your response MUST be a single fenced JSON block in the following format:\n   137→\n   138→```json\n   139→{\n   140→  \"missing_fields\": [\n   141→    {\"field\": \"field_name\", \"description\": \"what information is missing\"}\n   142→  ],\n   143→  \"ambiguities\": [\n   144→    {\"area\": \"area_name\", \"description\": \"what is unclear or ambiguous\"}\n   145→  ],\n   146→  \"questions\": [\n   147→    {\n   148→      \"key\": \"unique_question_key\",\n   149→      \"prompt\": \"Question to ask the user?\",\n   150→      \"kind\": \"FreeText\",\n   151→      \"suggested_default\": null,\n   152→      \"impact_stage\": \"{{impact_stage}}\"\n   153→    }\n   154→  ],\n   155→  \"suggested_defaults\": [\n   156→    {\"key\": \"default_key\", \"value\": \"default_value\", \"rationale\": \"why this default\"}\n   157→  ]\n   158→}\n   159→```\n   160→\n   161→Valid values for `kind`: \"FreeText\", {\"Choice\": [\"option1\", \"option2\"]}, \"YesNo\"\n   162→Valid values for `impact_stage`: \"Ideation\", \"Research\", \"Synthesis\", \"Prd\"\n   163→\n   164→If there are no gaps, return an empty structure with empty arrays for all fields.\n   165→\"#;\n   166→\n   167→const VALIDATION_PROMPT: &str = r#\"You are a PRD reviewer. Validate the following final PRD for completeness and clarity.\n   168→\n   169→**Product Idea:**\n   170→{{idea}}\n   171→\n   172→**User-Provided Context:**\n   173→{{answers}}\n   174→\n   175→**Final PRD:**\n   176→{{prd}}\n   177→\n   178→**Task:**\n   179→Review the PRD and determine if it is complete and ready for implementation. Check that all required sections are present, substantive, and free of critical gaps.\n   180→\n   181→**Required Output Format:**\n   182→Your response MUST be a single fenced JSON block in the following format:\n   183→\n   184→```json\n   185→{\n   186→  \"valid\": true,\n   187→  \"issues\": []\n   188→}\n   189→```\n   190→\n   191→If the PRD has issues, set `valid` to `false` and list each issue:\n   192→\n   193→```json\n   194→{\n   195→  \"valid\": false,\n   196→  \"issues\": [\n   197→    {\"field\": \"field_name\", \"description\": \"what is missing or unclear\"}\n   198→  ]\n   199→}\n   200→```\n   201→\"#;\n   202→\n   203→// ============================================================================\n   204→// Required Sections Per Stage\n   205→// ============================================================================\n   206→\n   207→fn required_sections(stage: Stage) -> &'static [&'static str] {\n   208→    match stage {\n   209→        Stage::Ideation => &[\n   210→            \"## Core Concept\",\n   211→            \"## Target Users\",\n   212→            \"## Key Problems Solved\",\n   213→            \"## Proposed Features\",\n   214→            \"## Success Metrics\",\n   215→            \"## Constraints & Assumptions\",\n   216→        ],\n   217→        Stage::Research => &[\n   218→            \"## Market Context\",\n   219→            \"## Technical Landscape\",\n   220→            \"## Comparable Solutions\",\n   221→            \"## Technical Feasibility\",\n   222→            \"## Risk Assessment\",\n   223→        ],\n   224→        Stage::Synthesis => &[\n   225→            \"## Product Vision\",\n   226→            \"## User Stories\",\n   227→            \"## Feature Prioritization\",\n   228→            \"## Architecture Overview\",\n   229→            \"## MVP Scope\",\n   230→            \"## Open Questions\",\n   231→        ],\n   232→        Stage::Prd => &[\n   233→            \"## Executive Summary\",\n   234→            \"## Goals & Non-Goals\",\n   235→            \"## User Stories\",\n   236→            \"## Functional Requirements\",\n   237→            \"## Non-Functional Requirements\",\n   238→            \"## Technical Architecture\",\n   239→            \"## Data Model\",\n   240→            \"## API Design\",\n   241→            \"## Security Considerations\",\n   242→            \"## Testing Strategy\",\n   243→            \"## Rollout Plan\",\n   244→            \"## Success Metrics\",\n   245→            \"## Open Questions\",\n   246→        ],\n   247→    }\n   248→}\n   249→\n   250→// ============================================================================\n   251→// Prompt Builder\n   252→// ============================================================================\n   253→\n   254→/// Builder for stage prompts with dependency injection.\n   255→pub struct StagePromptBuilder {\n   256→    idea: String,\n   257→    answers: BTreeMap<String, String>,\n   258→    stage_outputs: BTreeMap<Stage, String>,\n   259→}\n   260→\n   261→impl StagePromptBuilder {\n   262→    /// Creates a new prompt builder with the given idea, answers, and prior stage outputs.\n   263→    pub fn new(\n   264→        idea: String,\n   265→        answers: BTreeMap<String, String>,\n   266→        stage_outputs: BTreeMap<Stage, String>,\n   267→    ) -> Self {\n   268→        Self {\n   269→            idea,\n   270→            answers,\n   271→            stage_outputs,\n   272→        }\n   273→    }\n   274→\n   275→    /// Builds the prompt for a specific stage, injecting prior stage outputs as dependencies.\n   276→    pub fn build_stage_prompt(&self, stage: Stage) -> String {\n   277→        let template = match stage {\n   278→            Stage::Ideation => IDEATION_PROMPT,\n   279→            Stage::Research => RESEARCH_PROMPT,\n   280→            Stage::Synthesis => SYNTHESIS_PROMPT,\n   281