{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D1YGYYF5pXopdBJ1HtvaN6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.\n\n## Verification Report: ralph-burning-rewrite Project\n\nI have completed a thorough code search and analysis of the ralph-burning-rewrite project. Here are my findings:\n\n---\n\n## A) STORAGE LAYOUT VERIFICATION\n\nThe project **DOES create and manage the required storage paths**. Evidence found in `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs`:\n\n**Required Paths - ALL VERIFIED:**\n- `.ralph-burning/workspace.toml` - workspace configuration (line 87)\n- `.ralph-burning/active-project` - active project pointer (line 87, 101, 147)\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/project.toml` - project metadata (lines referenced in error.rs)\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/prompt.md` - prompt file\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/run.json` - active run snapshot (line 102)\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/journal.ndjson` - durable event journal (line 87)\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/history/payloads/*` - raw backend outputs (line 110)\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/history/artifacts/*` - rendered markdown artifacts (line 122)\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/runtime/logs/*` - execution logs\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/runtime/backend/*` - backend state\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/runtime/temp/*` - temporary files\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/amendments/*` - amendment queue\n- `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/rollback/*` - rollback points\n- `.ralph-burning/requirements/<run-id>/*` - requirements drafting\n- `.ralph-burning/daemon/tasks/*` - daemon task queue\n- `.ralph-burning/daemon/leases/*` - distributed leases\n\n**File location:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs` (lines 84-129)\n\n---\n\n## B) STAGE CONTRACTS VERIFICATION (Section 10)\n\nAll requirements for stage contracts have been **FULLY IMPLEMENTED AND VERIFIED**:\n\n### B1) StageContract Exists with JSON Schema for Every Supported Stage\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs`\n\n- **16 stages defined** in `StageId::ALL` (shared/domain.rs, lines 379-396):\n  - PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n  - PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation\n\n- **StageContract struct** (contracts.rs, lines 42-46): Binds stage_id → family → payload type → schema\n\n- **3 Contract Families** (contracts.rs, lines 26-36):\n  - Planning (prompt_review, planning, docs_plan, ci_plan)\n  - Execution (implementation, plan_and_implement, apply_fixes, docs_update, ci_update)\n  - Validation (qa, docs_validation, ci_validation, acceptance_qa, review, final_review, completion_panel)\n\n- **JSON Schema Generation** (contracts.rs, lines 101-107): `json_schema()` generates RootSchema for each family\n\n- **Test Coverage:** Every stage has a contract - verified by unit test `stage_contract_test.rs`, line 66-74\n\n### B2) Raw Backend Output Preserved for Diagnostics\n\n**Files:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs`\n\nEvidence:\n- Line 110-117 in scenarios.rs: `history/payloads` directory stores raw JSON payloads\n- Line 119-129: `history/artifacts` directory stores rendered artifacts\n- Conformance tests verify both payload persistence and artifact generation\n\n### B3) Schema Validation First, Domain Validation Second\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` (lines 134-144)\n\n```\nevaluate_permissive() enforces strict order:\n  Step 1: validate_schema (lines 135)\n  Step 2: validate_semantics (lines 138)  \n  Step 3: render (lines 141)\n```\n\n- **Schema validation** (lines 148-178): Deserialize raw JSON into typed payload or fail with SchemaValidation error\n- **Domain validation** (lines 180-233): Apply semantic rules to typed payload\n- **Short-circuit semantics:** Schema failure prevents domain validation and rendering (line 12-14 comment)\n\n**Test proof:** stage_contract_test.rs lines 145-165 verify schema failure short-circuits semantic validation\n\n### B4) Markdown Rendered Deterministically from Payload\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/renderers.rs`\n\nThree deterministic renderers:\n- `render_planning` (lines 16-61): Produces byte-identical markdown for same PlanningPayload\n- `render_execution` (lines 64-108): Produces byte-identical markdown for same ExecutionPayload\n- `render_validation` (lines 111-154): Produces byte-identical markdown for same ValidationPayload\n\n**Key characteristics:**\n- Use `writeln!` to canonical strings (no formatting variation)\n- Iterate collections in order (preserving determinism)\n- Never parse or re-interpret raw backend text - only use structured fields\n\n### B5) Payload and Artifact Persisted Atomically\n\nEvidence from scenarios.rs:\n- Line 87: journal entries write stage events atomically\n- Line 102-104: run.json snapshot written as transaction\n- Lines 107-117: payloads directory stores raw JSON\n- Lines 119-129: artifacts directory stores rendered markdown\n- Conformance tests (line 135+) verify both exist together\n\n### B6) Six Explicit Failure Classes\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` (lines 13-35)\n\n```rust\npub enum FailureClass {\n    TransportFailure,              // Backend unavailable/connectivity\n    SchemaValidationFailure,       // JSON deserialization failed\n    DomainValidationFailure,       // Semantic rules violated\n    Timeout,