e/src/shared/domain.rs` lines 486-550\n- `StageCursor::new()` validates cycle >= 1, attempt >= 1, completion_round >= 1\n- `retry()` increments only attempt, preserves cycle and completion_round\n- `advance_cycle()` increments cycle and resets attempt to 1\n- `advance_completion_round()` increments completion_round independently\n- Both cycle and completion_round are u32 and can only increase (monotonic enforcement via method design)\n\n**5. Structured payload validation before any state mutation - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` lines 109-144\n- `StageContract::evaluate()` enforces validation order:\n  - Step 1: Schema validation (line 135)\n  - Step 2: Semantic validation (line 138)\n  - Step 3: Rendering (line 141)\n- No state persisted until `ValidatedBundle` is created successfully\n- Comment on line 11-14 explicitly documents this invariant\n\n**6. Domain validation after schema validation, before transition commit - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` lines 180-233\n- `validate_semantics()` is called after `validate_schema()` (line 138)\n- Semantic validation includes domain rules like non-empty fields, positive order values, required follow-ups\n- Rendering only occurs after both validations pass (line 141)\n\n**7. Durable project history = journal + payloads + rendered artifacts only - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` lines 168-214\n- `JournalEvent` stored in `journal.ndjson` (lines 169-175)\n- `PayloadRecord` stored in `history/payloads/` (lines 196-204)\n- `ArtifactRecord` stored in `history/artifacts/` (lines 207-214)\n- Runtime logs explicitly separated into `RuntimeLogEntry` struct (lines 217-223)\n\n**8. Runtime logs are never promoted into durable history - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` lines 71-78\n- `RuntimeLogStorePort` explicitly separated from artifact/journal ports\n- Line 145-152: `RuntimeLogWritePort` marked as \"best-effort, not durable history\"\n- Lines 397-405: `run_history()` explicitly excludes runtime logs from durable history\n- Lines 422-454: `run_tail()` includes logs separately only when `include_logs=true`\n\n**9. Run start on project with active run must resume or fail (no duplicate active runs) - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` lines 286-290\n- Guard check: `if snapshot.has_active_run()` returns error\n- Error: \"project already has an active run\"\n- Lines 267-285: RunStatus checks prevent starting when status is Failed/Paused (requires resume)\n- Lines 554-562: Resume rejects Running status (prevents duplicates)\n\n**10. Resume only from durable stage boundaries - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` lines 476-494\n- `get_rollback_point_for_stage()` retrieves only durable rollback points\n- Rollback points are explicitly durable (lines 234-244 in model.rs)\n- Resume reconstructs from `rollback_point.run_snapshot` (line 545)\n- Lines 521-527: Stage must be in flow definition before resuming\n\n**11. Terminal state transitions persist before cleanup - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` lines 1950-1960\n- `complete_run()`: Line 1954 persists snapshot BEFORE journal event line 1960\n- Lines 1994-2004 in `fail_run()`: Snapshot persisted (line 1997) BEFORE journal attempt (line 2003)\n- Lines 1971-1974 in `pause_run()`: Snapshot persistence is the function call itself\n- All three functions establish durable terminal state first\n\n**12. Explicit model overrides trump role defaults - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs` lines 43-62\n- `BackendResolver::resolve()` applies overrides in order:\n  - Line 52-53: Apply workspace defaults\n  - Line 55-56: Apply project config\n  - Line 58-59: Apply explicit model override LAST (trumps previous)\n- Lines 94-98: `apply_model_override()` unconditionally sets the model\n\n**13. Session reuse only for roles/backends that explicitly allow it - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` lines 107-126\n- `CapabilityMetadata` contains `supports_session_reuse: bool`\n- Lines 137-141: OpenRouter marked as non-reusable\n- Lines 252-254: `BackendRole::allows_session_reuse()` returns true only for Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator\n- Lines 203-205: `ResolvedBackendTarget::supports_session_reuse()` checks both backend AND model\n\n**14. Cancellation and timeout must immediately halt retries - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs` lines 18-46\n- `CancellationToken` provides `is_cancelled()` and `cancel()` with `SeqCst` atomics\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` lines 1510-1527\n- Loop checks `if cancellation_token.is_cancelled()` before each retry (line 1510)\n- Immediate `fail_run_result()` when cancelled (lines 1511-1526)\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/retry_policy.rs` lines 45-46\n- `Cancellation` and `Timeout` both marked as `terminal()` (non-retryable)\n\n**15. One writer lock per project - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/lease_service.rs` lines 44-45\n- `store.acquire_writer_lock(base_dir, project_id, &lease_id)` called during lease acquisition\n- Lines 52, 69, 105: Lock explicitly released in error paths\n- Lines 149-152: Lock prevents duplicate lease acquisition (checked before claiming)\n\n**16. One active daemon task per issue - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs` lines 48-53\n- `create_task()` checks: `.any(|task| task.issue_ref == issue_ref && !task.is_terminal())`\n- Returns `DuplicateTaskForIssue` error if non-terminal task exists\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/model.rs` lines 165-169\n- `is_active_for_issue()` returns true only for non-terminal tasks\n\n**17. One worktree lease per task - CONFIRMED**\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/lease_service.rs` lines 32-42\n- Guard: `.any(|lease| lease.task_id == task_id)` rejects duplicate leases\n- Returns error if lease already exists\n- Location: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs` lines 124-135\n- Double-check: both task.lease_id and store.list_leases verified before claiming\n\n### SUMMARY\n\nAll 17 core invariants from Section 7 are **verified to be enforced in code**. The implementation demonstrates:\n\n- Strong type system enforcement (e.g., `Option<ActiveRun>`, immutable ProjectRecord.flow)\n- Explicit validation guards at critical transitions\n- Clear separation of concerns (ports, services, models)\n- Deterministic ordering of operations (validation → mutation → persistence)\n- Atomic operations and state management patterns\n- Durable history properly isolated from runtime state\n\nThe codebase shows sophisticated invariant enforcement through:\n- Constructor validation for cursor fields\n- Port-based abstraction for durable vs runtime storage\n- Transaction-like patterns (persist terminal state before cleanup)\n- Explicit terminal/non-terminal state machines\n- Retry policies keyed to failure classes\n- Capability-based session reuse decisions"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa6b531af53